"{\"uid\": \"washingtontimes.com-news-2024-aug-5-taiwan-seeks-investigation-into-fan-at-olympic-bad\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"TAIPEI,Taiwan(AP) -Taiwan'sgovernment on Monday called on French authorities to investigate an incident at the Paris Olympics men's doubles badminton final againstChinawhen aTaiwansupporter had her sign reading, \\\"Let us goTaiwan,\\\" ripped from her hands and torn up.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"score\": 0.9786853617471456, \"rank\": 0.021626171648630756, \"text\": \"TAIPEI\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 58, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7889272303563488, \"rank\": 0.150921576892593, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Taiwan Foreign Ministry described the incident as violent and against the Olympic values of friendship and respect.\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999993456186, \"rank\": 4.675270941173057e-10, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 278, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_of_the_People's_Republic_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9999996931581352, \"rank\": 2.8770876242563123e-07, \"text\": \"Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_of_the_People's_Republic_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_of_the_People's_Republic_of_China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A towel with a similar sentiment was also stolen from a fan during the match, in whichTaiwan'sLee Yang and Wang Chi-Lin beatChina'sLiang Wei Keng and Wang Chang to win gold.\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 494, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chi-lin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Chi-Lin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chi-lin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chi-lin\"}, {\"begin\": 524, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"score\": 0.9994363145831539, \"rank\": 0.0004492615148677608, \"text\": \"Wei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\"}, {\"begin\": 537, \"end\": 547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Jipeng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9992489654277784e-16, \"text\": \"Wang Chang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Jipeng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Jipeng\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Badminton World Federation did not immediately respond to a message seeking comment on the situation.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Badminton World Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee spokesperson Mark Adams cited the 1981 agreement forTaiwanto participate as ChineseTaipeiwhen asked about the incident.\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": [{\"beg