ittees together in one place.\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is quite a tough ask.\\\"\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ChinaclaimsTaiwanas its own territory to be annexed by force if necessary and rejects all manifestations of the island's independent identity.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chinese students and undercover officers living abroad are frequently deployed to disrupt support forTaiwan, Hong Kong, Tibet and the traditionally Muslim northwestern region of Xinjiang, according toTaiwan'sde-facto ambassador to France, Wu Chih-chung.\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9498531720298962, \"rank\": 0.05263331880565404, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}, {\"begin\": 1417, \"end\": 1422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tibet\", \"score\": 0.9207492009620981, \"rank\": 0.08582153269501361, \"text\": \"Tibet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tibet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tibet\"}, {\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_China\", \"score\": 0.9976030835127787, \"rank\": 0.002377949217771553, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1475, \"end\": 1483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinjiang\", \"score\": 0.9686897502405812, \"rank\": 0.03232221726735111, \"text\": \"Xinjiang\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinjiang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinjiang\"}, {\"begin\": 1536, \"end\": 1549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Chih-ch